OL,6,FAs part of the probe an SIA
OL,7,Finvestigator wrote to Mr Bryson
OL,8,Frequesting information about the
OL,9,Fcompany.
OL,11,FIn his reply the high-profile loyalist
OL,12,Fstated that JJ Security Services Ltd
OL,13,Fhas never traded and he does not hold
OL,14,Fany relevant information.
OL,16,FMr Bryson faced a charge of making a
OL,17,Ffalse statement to the authority.
OL,19,FDenying any wrongdoing, he argued that
OL,20,Fthe SIA's powers did not extend to
OL,21,FNorthern Ireland.
