OL,3,C'Legal errors' made in Jamie Bryson
OL,4,Ccase, Appeal Court rules
OL,6,FCentral to his defence was a further
OL,7,Fcontention that the chair of the body
OL,8,Fhad no right under the Private
OL,9,FSecurity Industry Act 2001 to delegate
OL,10,Fauthority to investigators who
OL,11,Fexamined his alleged activities.
OL,13,FIn August last year Mr Bryson
OL,14,Fsucceeded in having the summons
OL,15,Fdismissed at a preliminary stage
OL,16,Ffocused on legal issues.
OL,18,FA district judge granted his
OL,19,Fapplication for a direction that he
OL,20,Fhad no case to answer based on doubts
OL,21,Fabout the validity of the process.
