OL,3,C'Legal errors' made in Jamie Bryson
OL,4,Ccase, Appeal Court rules
OL,6,FAs the SIA mounted a challenge to her
OL,7,Fdetermination, the Court of Appeal was
OL,8,Fasked to rule on the conclusions she
OL,9,Freached.
OL,11,FCounsel for the authority insisted
OL,12,Fthere was a lawful and proper
OL,13,Fdelegation in the case.
OL,15,FMr Bryson, who represented himself in
OL,16,Fthe appeal, argued that those powers
OL,17,Fonly remained with the body corporate.
OL,1,Wj5k7j5                          G6/9
