OL,3,C'Legal errors' made in Jamie Bryson
OL,4,Ccase, Appeal Court rules
OL,6,FBut Lord Justice Treacy, sitting with
OL,7,FLord Justice Horner, held that the
OL,8,FDistrict Judge had "erred in law" in
OL,9,Fher legal assessment.
OL,11,F"The chair did have authority to
OL,12,Fdelegate the power on behalf of the
OL,13,Fauthority," he said.
OL,15,FLord Justice Treacy further confirmed:
OL,16,F"We agree that the District Judge was
OL,17,Fincorrect to conclude that there was a
OL,18,Fdoubt as to whether the delegation had
OL,19,Feffect in Northern Ireland."
